x4freetext: The Relative Accuracy of the Cross Sections Given is
Estimated to be Better Than 10% with the
Exception For the Highest and the Low Deuteron Energies
Where It can Amount to As Much As 40%. Included are
Errors in the Determination of the Beam Current, the
Energy of the Deuterons, the Yield, and the Statistics
Of the Activity Measurements.
Not Included are Errors of the Monitor, and the Decay
Data.
Saturation Production Rates were Calculted For 11.7
And 13.0 MeV on the Basis of the Cross Sections Given.
Lapf
Some Corrections have Been Included by
CAJAD
Reaction Lines are Corrected.
Last checking has been done.

x4freetext: The Thick Target Yields were Calculated by Integrating
The Differential Cross Sections Measured from a Stack.
Resolution 2.6 KeV (FWHM) At 1332.5 KeV
100% Isomeric Transition;  Comment
By the Compiler of Kachapag.
The Degradation of the Energy was Calculated According
To C.Williamson Et Al., Cea-2189(1962).
The Beam Current was Determined by Means of a Faraday
Cup, Calorimetrically and by Means of a Monitor
Reaction.
Stack 1 Consisting of Mo-Foils of 17.82 Mg/Cm**2 and
Al-Foils of 3.02 Mg/Cm**2 For Beam Monitoring and the
Determination of Recoils. Purity of the Mo-Foils
Higher Than 99%, Impurity 150 Ppm of Tungsten
Found by Activation Analysis. No Impurities of Elements
With Atomic Numbers Higher Than 22 Could be Detected
By X-Ray Fluorescence Analysis.
The Stack was Irradiated with Deuterons of 13.5 MeV
Incident Energy.
Stack 2 Consisting of Mo-Foils of 20.37 Mg/Cm**2 with
The Following Impurities (GIVEN IN PPM) 1420 W, 10 Ta,
17 Co, 13 Hg, 3.3 Th, and 50 Fe.
The Stack was Irradiated with Deuterons of 12.0 MeV
Incident Energy.
Obtained from a Foil of Stack 1
Obtained from a Foil of Stack 2

x4freetext: The Thick Target Yields were Calculated by Integrating

The Authors Assumed the Reaction Mo-97(D,A) Without
An Appreciable Contribution from Reactions with Other
Mo-Isotopes. `Since Above About 7 MeV the Reaction
(P,A+N) From the Neighbouring Isotope with Even
Larger Abundance Contributes Increasingly the Reaction
Was Coded Preferably As Mo-0(D,X) (COMMENT BY THE
COMPILER).` Since the Authors have Corrected the
Original Data For the Isotopic Abundance of Mo-97,
The Values Given in the Data Section have to be
Recorrected For the Natural Target. This Statement
Refers Only to the Cross Sections Given in the Data
Section, But not to the Thick Target Yields Which
Correspond Obviously to a Natural Mo-Target.
